properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 8 at 4:15AM PST until February 9 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Gusty North to East Wind Sunday...

.Low pressure brings a period of strong north to east wind over
portions of interior Northern California Sunday. Wind begins to
increase later today into tonight, with the strongest wind Sunday
morning into evening. Highest wind speeds are expected along the
west side of the Sacramento Valley extending into the Coastal
Range, and over portions of the Sierra Nevada. Wind speeds
decrease Sunday night, but remain breezy into Monday.

* WHAT...North to east wind 20 to 35 mph. Wind gusts up to 50 mph
possible in the Central Valley Sunday. Wind gusts locally up to
60 mph or higher in Coastal Range and Sierra Nevada.

* WHERE...Sacramento Valley, Carquinez Strait and Delta, Northern
San Joaquin Valley, Coastal range from Western Shasta County to
Lake County, Western Plumas County and West Slopes of the
Northern Sierra Nevada.

* WHEN...From 10 AM to 10 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty wind could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and power outages may result.
Difficult driving conditions for small and high profile
vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Northerly wind may cause downed trees in
the Delta region due to non-prevailing wind direction. Strong
easterly wind could impact outdoor recreational activities in
the Sierra Nevada.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM TO 10 PM PST SUNDAY
